Mutable vs Immutable

Mutable Objects
Mutbale objects are the objects whose state can change after creation.

Example:-
lst = [1,2,3]
lst.append(4)
print(lst)
Output:- [1,2,3,4]

Immutbale objects
Immutable objects are the objects whose state/value cannot be changed/modified afer creation.

Example:- 
int
float
str
tuple
frozenset
bool

Example:-
x = 10
x = x + 1

Here, x will point to 10
However now, x will refrence to new object 11.
Python does not modify 10.

Memory behavior

Example:-

a = [1,2]
b = a
a.append(3)

print(a)
output:- [1,2,3]
Here, both variables points to same object.
i.e a = [1,2,3]
b = [1,2,3]

But with immutbale:
a = 10
b = a
a = 20
print(a)
print(b)

Output:- 
a = 20
b = 10

Why immutbale objects matter
Benefits:- 
Safer
hasable
Can be used as keys in dictionary
threat-safe

Example:- 
my_datab = {
   (1,2): "Value"
}
